The paper presents an algorithm for constructing a context-free grammar for compressing an input string, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm's analysis uses a general technique of recompression, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with approximation guarantees, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
